  "events": [
    {
      "trigger": "enter_from_blackthorn",
      "description": "Route 45 can only be entered from the north (Blackthorn City). Ledges throughout the route prevent northward travel. Players must use Fly or go through Blackthorn to repeat the route."
    },
    {
      "trigger": "talk_blackbelt_kenji_post_battle",
      "description": "Blackbelt Kenji asks for the player's phone number. Calls mid-day to offer PP Up gift when on break (EVENT_KENJI_ON_BREAK). Has morning/night dialogue variants."
    },
    {
      "trigger": "talk_hiker_parry_post_battle",
      "description": "Hiker Parry asks for the player's phone number. Pokegear rematch contact. Rewards Iron on final third rematch (PARRY2 team)."
    },
    {
      "trigger": "dark_cave_blackthorn_entrance_warp",
      "description": "The Dark Cave entrance at (2,5) leads to DARK_CAVE_BLACKTHORN_ENTRANCE \u2014 the western section of Dark Cave, which requires Flash and has Lv20-30 encounters including Wobbuffet and Ursaring (Gold)."
    }
  ],
  "notes": "Route 45 is the longest route in Johto at 10x45 blocks (20x90 tiles). It descends south from Blackthorn City's southern gate through rugged mountain terrain to connect with Route 46. One-way ledges appear repeatedly throughout \u2014 players can only travel south. The route is notable for Dratini fishing (Good Rod 10%, Super Rod 30%) and Dragonair (Super Rod 10%) in the central pond. Dark Cave has its Blackthorn entrance here. The route splits into multiple narrow rock-ledge corridors at various points with tall grass in between. pokecrystal object constants: ROUTE45_POKEFAN_M1=HikerErik, ROUTE45_POKEFAN_M2=HikerMichael, ROUTE45_POKEFAN_M3=HikerParry, ROUTE45_POKEFAN_M4=HikerTimothy, ROUTE45_BLACK_BELT=BlackbeltKenji, ROUTE45_COOLTRAINER_M=CooltrainermRyan, ROUTE45_COOLTRAINER_F=CooltrainerfKelly, ROUTE45_YOUNGSTER=CamperQuentin. Note: despite using POKEFAN_M sprite constants for some hikers in the object_const_def, the actual trainer classes are HIKER."
}